{
  "type": "support_page",
  "title": "Screenshot Requirements – IS3513",
  "htmlTitle": "Screenshot Requirements – IS3513",
  "accentColor": "#E63946",
  "headerKeyword": "screenshot",
  "headerSecondary": "requirements",
  "headerSubtitle": "Evidence Standards for Lab Submissions",
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "intro",
      "html": "Screenshots are <strong style=\"color:#ffffff;\">evidence</strong>. In professional security work, undocumented claims don&#8217;t exist. Every screenshot must prove <em>you</em> did the work on <em>your</em> system."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout_bar",
      "color": "#E63946",
      "colorRgb": "230, 57, 70",
      "label": "Deduction:",
      "html": "<strong style=\"color:#ffffff;\">&#8722;5%</strong> per missing or unverifiable screenshot. No VM name visible? Wrong filename? Missing required capture? Each one costs you."
    },
    {
      "type": "two_column",
      "style": "detailed",
      "left": {
        "color": "#00D26A",
        "label": "✓ Verifiable Screenshot",
        "items": [
          { "title": "VM name in terminal prompt", "desc": "kali-lastname-abc123 visible" },
          { "title": "VM name in window title bar", "desc": "hostname visible at top" },
          { "title": "Hostname visible in command output", "desc": "e.g., uname -n output" }
        ]
      },
      "right": {
        "color": "#E63946",
        "label": "✗ Unverifiable Screenshot",
        "items": [
          { "title": "Generic \"kali@kali\" prompt", "desc": "default name, not yours" },
          { "title": "Cropped to hide hostname", "desc": "partial screenshots rejected" },
          { "title": "Web browser only, no VM context", "desc": "could be anyone&#8217;s machine" }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "named_section",
      "color": "#FF9F1C",
      "label": "Critical: VM Name Visibility",
      "paragraphs": [
        "Your VM must be named <code style=\"background:#1a1f2e;padding:3px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:13px;color:#FF9F1C;\">kali-lastname-studentID</code> and this name must be visible in every screenshot.",
        "Without your VM name, there&#8217;s no way to verify <em>you</em> ran the commands. Screenshots without identification could be copied from anywhere &#8212; and occasionally are."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "named_section",
      "color": "#4169E1",
      "label": "Filename Convention",
      "paragraphs": [
        "All screenshots follow this naming pattern: <code style=\"background:#1a1f2e;padding:3px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:13px;color:#4169E1;\">##-description.png</code>"
      ],
      "items": [
        "<code style=\"background:#1a1f2e;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:13px;color:#4169E1;\">01-vm-settings.png</code> &#8212; First screenshot, VM configuration",
        "<code style=\"background:#1a1f2e;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:13px;color:#4169E1;\">07-nmap-scan-results.png</code> &#8212; Seventh screenshot, nmap output",
        "<code style=\"background:#1a1f2e;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-family:Consolas,monospace;font-size:13px;color:#4169E1;\">15-wireshark-tcp-stream.png</code> &#8212; Fifteenth screenshot, Wireshark analysis"
      ],
      "tip": "Two-digit numbers keep files sorted correctly (01, 02&#8230; not 1, 2, 10, 11). This matters when you&#8217;re compiling 20+ screenshots into a report."
    },
    {
      "type": "two_column",
      "style": "simple",
      "left": {
        "color": "#00D26A",
        "label": "Always Capture",
        "items": [
          "Command you ran",
          "Output / results",
          "VM name visible (terminal prompt or title)",
          "Relevant context (IP addresses, tool version, etc.)"
        ]
      },
      "right": {
        "color": "#7B68EE",
        "label": "When Instructed",
        "items": [
          "Error messages (document failures too)",
          "Configuration screens",
          "Before/after comparisons",
          "Specific UI elements"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "named_section",
      "color": "#00BCD4",
      "label": "Folder Organization",
      "paragraphs": [
        "Keep screenshots organized by lab in your Kali VM:"
      ],
      "code_block": "~/Screenshots/\n├── Lab1-Screenshots/\n│   ├── 01-vm-settings.png\n│   ├── 02-kali-desktop.png\n│   └── ...\n├── Lab2-Screenshots/\n├── Lab3-Screenshots/\n└── ..."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout_bar",
      "color": "#00D26A",
      "colorRgb": "0, 210, 106",
      "label": "Pro Tip:",
      "html": "<strong>Screenshot as you go.</strong> Don&#8217;t try to recreate screenshots after the fact. Take them in real-time as you work. Missing a screenshot means redoing the work &#8212; or taking the deduction."
    },
    {
      "type": "footer",
      "html": "Every screenshot is evidence. Make it count."
    }
  ]
}
